{{distinguish|Pa Na language|Hamer-Banna language}} {{Infobox language |name=Bana |states=[[Cameroon]] |region=[[Far North Province]] |speakers=23,000 |date=2007 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Chadic languages|Chadic]] |fam3=[[Biu–Mandara languages|Biu–Mandara]] |fam4=Bura–Higi |fam5=[[Higi languages|Higi]] (A.3) |iso3=bcw |glotto=bana1305 |glottorefname=Bana }}
'''Bana''' is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in northern [[Cameroon]]. Dialects include Gamboura and Gili.<ref name=e18/>
==Phonology== {|class="IPA wikitable" |+Consonants ! ||[[Labial consonant|Labial]]||[[Alveolar consonant|Alveolar]]||[[Palatal consonant|Palatal]]||[[Velar consonant|Velar]]||[[Labialized velar consonant|Labialized velar]]||[[Uvular consonant|Uvular]]||[[Labialized]] uvular||[[Glottal consonant|Glottal]] |- ![[Nasal consonant|Nasal]] | m || n || || ŋ || ŋʷ || || || |- ![[Voiceless consonant|Voiceless]] [[plosive]] | p || t || || k || kʷ || || || ʔ ʔʷ |- ![[Voiced consonant|Voiced]] plosive | b || d || || ɡ || ɡʷ || || || |- ![[Prenasalized]] plosive | mb || nd ndz || || ŋɡ || ŋɡʷ || || || |- ![[Implosive consonant|Implosive]] | ɓ || ɗ || || || || || || |- ![[Affricate]] | || ts dz || || || || || || |- ![[Fricative]] | f v || s z || || || || χ ʁ || χʷ ʁʷ || |- ![[Flapping|Flap]] | ⱱ || ɾ || || || || || || |- ![[Approximant]] | || || j || || w || || || |}
The vowels of Bana are /ɨ ə ɛ/, which can occur with high, falling, low, or rising tone. <ref>Hofmann, Erica. 1990. A preliminary phonology of bana. University of Victoria. (MA thesis).</ref>
