[[File:Stabroek Market.JPG|thumb|300px|[[Stabroek Market]], [[Georgetown, Guyana|Georgetown]].]] '''Crime in Guyana''' is investigated by Guyana's police.
== Crime by type ==
=== Murder === {{Further|List of countries by intentional homicide rate}}
In 2012, Guyana had a murder rate of 17.0 per 100 000 population.<ref name=UNODC/> There were a total of 135 murders in Guyana in 2012.<ref name=UNODC>[https://www.unodc.org/gsh/en/index.html ''Global Study on Homicide''. [[United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime]], 2013.]</ref>
=== Domestic violence === {{Further|Domestic violence in Guyana}}
Domestic violence is a problem in all [[regions of Guyana]]. Enforcement of the domestic violence laws is especially weak in the interior, where police do not have as strong a presence and courts meet only once a quarter.<ref name=report>[https://www.state.gov/g/drl/rls/hrrpt/2006/78894.htm Report on Human Rights Practices 2006: Guyana]. [[United States]] [[Bureau of Democracy, Human Rights, and Labor]] (March 6, 2007). ''This article incorporates text from this source, which is in the [[public domain]].''</ref>
[[NGOs]] report a widespread perception that some police officers and magistrates could be [[bribed]] to make cases of domestic violence "go away." The government also does not prosecute cases in which the alleged victim or victim's family agreed to drop the case in exchange for a monetary payment [[Settlement (litigation)|out of court]]. NGOs assert the need for a specialized Family Court.<ref name=report/>
=== Robbery === Armed robberies occur regularly, especially in businesses and shopping districts, especially in the capital [[Georgetown, Guyana|Georgetown]].<ref>[https://www.osac.gov/pages/ContentReportDetails.aspx?cid=16163 "Guyana 2014 Crime and Safety Report", Overseas Security Advisory Council, US State Department, 15 August 2014.]</ref> Nationally, there were 512 robberies under arms during the period January to October 2012 (a 15% increase from 2011).<ref>[https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/guyana/safety-and-security "Guyana travel advice - Safety and security", United Kingdom Government foreign travel advice.]</ref>
== By location == === Georgetown === In Georgetown, high crime areas include Tiger Bay, Albouystown, Sophia, all of south Georgetown, [[Buxton, Guyana|Buxton]] and Agricola.<ref>[https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/guyana/safety-and-security "Guyana travel advice - Safety and security", United Kingdom Government foreign travel advice.]</ref> Robberies are a daily occurrence in the [[Stabroek Market]] area.<ref>[https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/guyana/safety-and-security "Guyana travel advice - Safety and security", United Kingdom Government foreign travel advice.]</ref> A number of assaults have taken place in the Botanic Gardens.<ref>[https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/guyana/safety-and-security "Guyana travel advice - Safety and security", United Kingdom Government foreign travel advice.]</ref>
