{{Infobox language |name=Guohe |nativename= |states=[[China]] |region=[[Yunnan]] |ethnicity=[[Hani people|Hani]] |speakers=? |date= |ref= |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=[[Hanoish languages|Southern Loloish]] |fam6=[[Hani languages|Hani]] |iso3=none |glotto=none }} '''Guohe''' ({{zh|郭合}}) is a [[Hanoish languages|Southern Loloish]] language of [[Yunnan]], China. It is spoken in Dengqu Village 登去村, Majie Township 马街乡, [[Yuanjiang County]] 元阳县, Yunnan (Wang 2011).<ref name="Guohe">[http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=198280 元阳县马街乡登云村委会]</ref> It is known as Guohong 郭宏 in [[Yuanyang County, Yunnan]] (''Yuanyang County Gazetteer'' 1990:625).<ref>Yuanyang County Gazetteer Editorial Committee (ed). 1990. ''Yuanyang County Gazetteer'' 元阳县志. Guiyang: Guizhou People’s Press 贵州民族出版社.</ref>
The Guohe language is documented in Wang (2011).
