'''Turks in Jordan''', also known as '''Jordanian Turks''' ({{lang-tr|Ürdün Türkleri}}), are people of [[Turkish people|Turkish]] ancestry living in [[Jordan]]. These people have had a thriving presence in [[Jordan]] since the rule of the [[Ottoman Empire]]. Today, there is a minority of about 60,000 people in the country who are the descendants of the [[Turkish people|Ottoman-Turkish]] immigrants.<ref name="Akar 1993 loc=95"/> In addition to this, there are also 8,262 [[Turkish people|Turkish citizens]] who are recent migrants to [[Jordan]].<ref name=CSGB/>

