{{Infobox organization |name = Young People's Front for Democracy and Justice |image = Young People's Front for Democracy and Justice logo.png |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = YPFDJ |motto = Victory to the Masses |formation = |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = |location = Various |region_served = |membership = |language = |leader_title = President |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = [[People's Front for Democracy and Justice]] |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = http://www.youngpfdj.org|http://www.youngpfdj.org] |remarks = }}
'''Young People's Front for Democracy and Justice''' ('''YPFDJ''') ({{lang-ti|ህዝባዊ ግንባር ንደሞክራስን ፍትሕን ን'ምንኦሰያት, Həzbawi Gənbar nəDämokrasən Fətəḥən, abbreviated ህግደፍ}}, {{lang-ar|الجبهة الشعبية للديمقراطية والعدالة}} ''al-Jabhatu l-Shaʻabiyatu lil-Dīmuqrāṭiyatu wāl-ʻIdālah'') is a nationalist [[Eritrea]]n Diaspora Youth organization branch of their parent organization, the '''People's Front for Democracy and Justice ''' ('''PFDJ'''), that is striving to create a strong, conscious, and nationalist youth movement.<ref>YPFDJ Website http://www.youngpfdj.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=53&Itemid=69</ref> Conferences are held throughout the world by local chapters, particularly in North America and Europe.<ref>All Africa News http://allafrica.com/stories/200809040094.html</ref>
Conferences have included both PFDJ dignitaries, members of the Eritrean government as well as non-Eritrean speakers.
